@SVK it seems that, since v1.0.8 it is actually required that the schemanode, for which you want to generate the artifact (in this case NetworkDevice) HAS to inherit from the CoreArtifactGeneric.

In versions prior to v1.0.8 this was optional

We failed to update our documentation and clearly communicate on this. Apologies for that.

```
{% if data.NetworkInterface.edges and data.NetworkInterface.edges is iterable %}
{% for interface in data["NetworkInterface"]["edges"] %}
{% set interface_name = interface.node.name.value %}
{% set interface_description = interface.node.description.value %}
{{ interface_name }}
   description: {{ interface_description }}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}
```

i am really just testing things out.. so its very very basic..

the query i have looks a little like this

```
query InterfaceQuery($hostname: String!) {
  NetworkInterface(device__hostname__value: $hostname) {
    edges {
        node {
            name {
            value
            }
            description {
            value
            }
        }
    }
  }
}
```
